  <name>Decode Orc</name>
  <summary>LaserDisc Workflow Orchestrator</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      Decode Orc is an orchestration and processing framework for LaserDisc and tape decoding workflows.
      It provides a node-based visual interface for building complex video processing pipelines.
    </p>
    <p>
      Features include:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Visual node-based workflow editor</li>
      <li>Support for TBC (Time Base Corrected) video files</li>
      <li>Field-based video processing</li>
      <li>Dropout correction and stacking</li>
      <li>VBI and EIA-608 closed caption decoding</li>
      <li>Source alignment for multi-source workflows</li>
    </ul>
  </description>
  <launchable type="desktop-id">io.github.simoninns.decode-orc.desktop</launchable>
